1463
01:55:18,699 --> 01:55:28,447
[SPEAKER_29]: So municipal aggregation, on every electric bill, there's a separate charge for the electricity supplied and charges for the distribution of the electricity.

1464
01:55:29,705 --> 01:55:35,710
[SPEAKER_29]: Massachusetts electricity has been deregulated in an effort to provide competition in the electricity market.

1465
01:55:35,930 --> 01:55:36,910
[SPEAKER_29]: This is not new.

1466
01:55:37,391 --> 01:55:44,176
[SPEAKER_29]: However, under Massachusetts law, electricity utilities only profit from the distribution charges.

1467
01:55:44,576 --> 01:55:47,819
[SPEAKER_29]: The supply charges are just a straight pass-through to them.

1468
01:55:48,439 --> 01:55:56,245
[SPEAKER_29]: Therefore, they don't benefit from supply, and our utility is perfectly happy that we get our electricity from whoever we want to.

1469
01:55:57,150 --> 01:56:02,712
[SPEAKER_29]: Large consumers of electricity take advantage of this and buy their electricity on the open market.

1470
01:56:03,073 --> 01:56:17,319
[SPEAKER_29]: Electricity is a commodity traded in this area, and the price fluctuates constantly and is dependent on many things, including how much you buy, the length of time of your contract, and the exact timing of when you make your purchase.

1471
01:56:18,879 --> 01:56:23,882
[SPEAKER_29]: As with any commodity, it goes up and down day to day, in fact, hour to hour.

1472
01:56:25,173 --> 01:56:27,174
[SPEAKER_29]: You can buy it on a spot market, in fact.

1473
01:56:27,754 --> 01:56:37,538
[SPEAKER_29]: The city has been buying electricity through a secondary supplier at a good time of year for us, aggregating our use and getting good pricing.

1474
01:56:38,359 --> 01:56:46,542
[SPEAKER_29]: And we usually sign contracts between one and three years, depending on what's being offered to us at the time, what's the best rate.

1475
01:56:47,283 --> 01:56:55,730
[SPEAKER_29]: So right now, National Grid purchases and supplies electricity to all of our residences that have not signed up with another supplier.

1476
01:56:56,250 --> 01:57:00,393
[SPEAKER_29]: However, the state regulates when National Grid can buy the electricity.

1477
01:57:01,174 --> 01:57:04,597
[SPEAKER_29]: They're limited to one specific day in October and one in April.

1478
01:57:05,317 --> 01:57:11,102
[SPEAKER_29]: As such, the price changes for our consumers twice a year, April and October.

1479
01:57:12,832 --> 01:57:30,057
