1480
01:57:31,738 --> 01:57:35,459
[SPEAKER_29]: So they are regulated by the state and do not get good

1481
01:57:35,889 --> 01:57:38,371
[SPEAKER_29]: the best prices possible for our residents.

1482
01:57:39,031 --> 01:57:51,180
[SPEAKER_29]: So municipal aggregation allows the city of Medford to contract with a consultant that would help us aggregate the volume of our residents and businesses who have not already done their own contract on their behalf.

1483
01:57:51,561 --> 01:58:00,167
[SPEAKER_29]: For example, Tufts University has already done this same process, and so they would not be part of this because they already contract for their supply.

1484
01:58:01,588 --> 01:58:02,749
[SPEAKER_29]: They would be able to do that.

1485
01:58:02,909 --> 01:58:04,450
[SPEAKER_29]: They would be able to time the market

1486
01:58:04,787 --> 01:58:07,689
[SPEAKER_29]: to make a strategic purchase on behalf of our residents.

1487
01:58:08,129 --> 01:58:13,433
[SPEAKER_29]: So they'd both be aggregated and the purchase would be timed to be best for them.

1488
01:58:14,313 --> 01:58:19,157
[SPEAKER_29]: And they would be able to look, we would look at the timing of that as well.

1489
01:58:19,737 --> 01:58:21,899
[SPEAKER_29]: And so how long the contract is.

1490
01:58:22,899 --> 01:58:25,441
[SPEAKER_29]: Sometimes you get a better rate if you commit to two years.

1491
01:58:25,681 --> 01:58:28,563
[SPEAKER_29]: Sometimes you get a better rate if you commit to one year.

1492
